column31: At first sight I thought this was a Brown Rat. Seemed huge for an MR, and quite plain, warm, brown upperparts (olive-brown fur with grey bases rather than grey with olive speckling). Not as scruffy and shaggy as MRs normally look but not sleek either.  Moderately long black guard hairs, no spines. Underparts warm creamy white deepening to buffy between legs. Tail all dark, ratio with HB is way too big for a Brown Rat but only just outside MR range, and too little for LTG. Prominent dark fur on top of feet, especially forefeet. Head and ear proportions seem to fit Jess's descriptions, colour is nowhere near LTG, and habitat very unlikely for BR, so I'm 90% happy this is a whopping Muller's (although only about halfway through the weight range in the mammal book!). Possibly the daddy of the family at 28 seen this week?
Another quite warm-coloured PR. I think they must just be browner than I remember them…
